content: Bought mConnect for my Samsung Note 20 Ultra and iPhone 11 Pro Max. The iOS version works seamlessly whe I use Tidal to stream into my Matrix Audio player. The Android version however does not respond at all.

Good app, but doesn't stream big files. I have no problem streaming large hi-res files using another app, but when using connect file above a certain resolution pause every 10 seconds while it buffers. The only difference in the whole system is mconnect, yet their support team deny all responsibility. A great shame, as otherwise a far superior app, but not much use to me if you can't stream hi-res files!
(‚ûñ) Gapless doesn't work on Tidal (didn't test other sources) (‚ûï) Nice looking interface (‚ûñ) Functionally kludgy

This is a great app for DLNA ready music streamers ,saves having different apps for different speakers.I have had issues with some speakers only playing one track of an album but that may be the speaker not the mconnect app overall really like this app . Recommendedüëç
Rarely launches Tidal properly. Always resorting to lite version
App is a great way to play Hi-Fi audio over WiFi. Sometime just a little glitchy dropping what's in the queue and requires a restart
Using mconnect seems to producer poorer sound quality as compare playing directly on tidal .
Super easy and fast initial set up. The interface is user friendly and looks very nice.
So far so good . Does precisely what I need it to.
TIDAL IS NOT WORKING AFTER UPDATE, PLEASE FIX IT
Good app but can no longer access Tidal, think it needs a fix? Was the best upnp app until this point.

I wish it would work as intended Interface is good, ease of use is Good.. On the face if it, it's a great app, but... You are able to listen to about 3 tracks until it crashes down. What good is a music controller app if it doesn't let you enjoy your music.
Very good and useful app but updates are bringing Tidal bugs all the time, such as track list not loading fully. Now the latest version don't even open Tidal. Please fix this!

I don't understand why this app can play Qobuz up to 96khz but will only play Tidal up to 48khz.this app isn't worth paying for. The free lite version will do the same.and clearly the developer doesn't care as they don't even respond to reviews or emails no support at all.
The best DLNA/UPNP app (probably)
It reliably streams to and from upnp servers. Qobuz and Tidal support is also good. The application always shows bit depth and sample rate that are in use

Since the last update, there are more things I don't like. The new tidal api is very sluggish. Maybe twice as slow as before. Only 50 songs are loaded in the favorite song section on the tidal, and you need to scroll down through the entire list to load it in the playlist. It's very hard and takes a long time, especially if you have more than, say, 500 songs. And we all mostly have more .. Please correct these errors, because the application has potential.
Doesn't gapless play properly, waste of time
Help needed to have better consistency with connecting to the AVR. 50% of the time its not showing up in the "play to" section.

I try to play a full album from Tidal browser but just the first track is played. I can see all tracks in the queue though. I use JRiver as DLNA renderer. Playing locally is OK but it is pointless (for this I can use Tifal app directly). I was told that the IOS app does not suffer this ... disappointing reallyfor the price. Did somebody reported this issue? Thanks
Good for stabbing MQA to my Oppo 205. But playing albums on Tidal it keeps pausing at the end of each track until I open the app again and asked next track.
App rarely list my Marantz SR8012 on the upnp list, while Spotify, Heos etc have no issues. Wrote to Customer Service for help, no reply...
Good hassle free app but shows invalid token even with valid ID and pw most if the time . Local files are not streamed to upnp renderers.

Excellent overall experience, MQA support and nice GUI. Only real criticism - Next / Previous buttons on my streamers (tried 4 different brands) don't work with M Connect. I'd be delighted is this gets resolved to make this a genuinely 5 star App.
Invalid token message fixed. Now just frequent unsupported file.

Can't open Tidal now. INVALID TOKEN it says. A quick email to developer, and they said they were going to look at the problem. A couple of hours later, problem solved. Although wasn't updated on the progress made.
Invalid token on tidal ? That's the reason I purchased this now it's useless üòí

Purchased the app a couple days ago and found it excellent value for what I paid for. Features and operating are handy for my music streaming on Tidal. What the shortcoming I found at this stage is that music files I store on Tidal cannot be played continously in sequence. When one file finishes, I have to mannualy select another music file.

Very good app. Only 2 issues. A click when starting next track with some renderers. Bel Canto eStream for me. An annoyance that may be tied to Quobuz as that service has handshake issues. Also the back control ago be placed lower on the screen. Waaay better than bubbleup as it doesn't run a faux upnp server that sucks up battery.
Very unstable, sometimes work fine sometimes doesn't work at all
Great app. Simple and effective. Perfect.
My Denon receiver keeps disapearing from Upnp devices on PlayTo tab. Both devices are on the same wifi network.

Player closes at the end of the current track if it doesn't have focus - either by switching to another app, or by switching off the screen to save battery. It also seems to limit output to 48khz when my Chromecast Audio can receive 96khz. Please help because the app is great otherwise. Only switched from Lite version to rectify this problem - it didn't. Hoping the developers see this and reply.

Finally an app that can stream Tidal MQA to my system, works with all Chromecast, Chromecast Ultra and Chromecast Audio and also work on my Denon receiver HEOS but instead it got down sampling to 48 kHz/24 bit.
Paid app does not save setting changes. Keeps resetting to default settings on every startup. I will get a refund and go back to free version until issue is fixed. Otherwise great app.

Connects to my renderer(pioneer N50) but when trying to stream tidal, shows an error message - file format not supported. Unable to resolve it. Bubbleupnp does the job. Purchased mconnect for tidal mqa but it doesn't seem to work with normal flac even
Developers have resolved an issue with Android 10 and this app. Works as expected with an easy to use interface

Good app, works flawlessy with mqa 24bit tracks when IGMP Multicast, and IGMP upstream/downstream in Edgeroiter-X is activated, Tidal MQA 24 bit 44.1/48/88.2/96 khz relies on working IGMP. Keep up the good work guys.

For little money this App is great. Using with my Cambridge CXN V2, because I don't like the USB set up via laptop.. The Cambridge App is OK, but doesn't work the same on PC. Getting 48.0khz on most music, and some MQA recorded much higher sounds great. Worth getting to know your way around if you have a Tidal hi fi account.
Decent app, any chance of adding Google drive to the cloud options?

I have been using the Lite version and just switched to the full version. I think this is great. It turned my Oppo UDP-205 into a Tidal streaming, MQA decoding and fantastic sounding component. I am listening to all kinds of new music in super high fidelity sound. All it took was this little 6 dollar app. Wow. Magnificent. Cool. ‚ò∫
Doesn't skip to next song, keeps repeating the same over and over even though changed to all different settings. Frustrating üò§
Grear audiophile tool to save hundreads of dollars !!! The only tool for sparky allo

Poor experience with app. Constant pausing of tracks. Customer service was also poor. They blamed everyone else even though my music never freezes using bubbleup. Waste of money, which they wouldn't refund!!

Keeps getting better. Like that the author keeps updating and improving! The interface isn't the best though... Hard to navigate, can't browse to artist or add to playlist from player screen, amongst others. Also please HIGHLIGHT the song currently playing in browse mode. It's hard to find when you would like to add it to a playlist or browser to album/artist.
Outdated interface is frustrating and none of my songs are in order despite them showing properly in every other player.
Only on a freak occasion will it see my Denon amp. Forcing a stop of the app sometimes resolves this but for a paid app this is not acceptable.

It gets the job done! Now I can push Tidal MQA to my OPPO UDP-205. Is it a perfect app? No, the UI style looks outdated and the alburm artwork is not centered in the screen. But there are more bugs in apps made by Chord or Cambridge Audio.

I would have given this app 3 stars but after the update one click of the volume rocker on the side of my phone turns up the device in increments of 20, had to physically go to the device and turn it down then turn it off. It was working fine before the update. The graphics poor and UI fiddly but it worked. This needs to be fixed.
The app isnt working after last update.
Used with Kef LS50W's - an exemplary app.
Audio quality wise, it's definitely better than Tidal's native player. However, the UI is far lacking what Tidal has. Some parts which are accessible via Tidal can't be done on this app.
Finally tidal master streaming to Chromecast and dlna

For some reason it doesn't see my UPnP server (Bubble does). The apps website is really light on information so currently I have no idea what to do with this problem. P.S. The app sees my server as a rendered, so they are on the same network .
no albumart!? it's constantly crashing, lite version didn't.. some tuner/radio support would be very welcome!

Please add ability to add a track to favorites on Tidal from the player. right now I have to search on Tidal for the track and manually add it, a hassle. Also needs "play from this point onward" and proper Google home voice control (can't even do "next track"). with these features I might give this 5 stars and would also pay significantly more. Still, a great value. Only other app I know of that can cast Tidal Masters is Roon and it requires a PC running its software, which costs hundreds of $.
Works with Tidal MQA. Other DLNA controllers don't. The best.

I love the fact that I can play tidal master quality from my smartphone, but the UI needs some improvements. When i press a song in the middle of a playlist, start that playlist from that song and onwards, not only that song. Add a "play next" feature. In shuffle-mode, the play queue should display the actual order of the songs. As of now, whenever i manually add songs to queue, the app just shuts down when the first song is completed (on yamaha rxa-2060).
Really like this app, does everything it says it does. Would have given it 5* if it had a landscape option, really needs this to work on a tablet.

Awesome app. I can now stream from jriver to Chromecast in high res!! Switch to my Tidal account with the press of a button. Even shows the bit rate. Well thought out and executed. If only it included radio as well this would be the only app you would ever need. Was going to buy an expensive streamer, don't need to now.
Best and cheapest way to get first unfold of mqa files on Tidal Masters without using TIDAL Desktop,I think Tidal should make people aware of it on their help pages
Can't find my aries g1. Plz help. Or. Fix
Sehr gut, bought it hehehe üëç
Mqa remote finally here :)

This an amazing music player, plays Tidal Master tracks, and has the M indicating the higher quality track. Best part is that it streams perfectly without skipping. Great easy to use UI as well. 5 stars
Good for dlna function to control jriver in home computer
Excellent app. Please add support for Deezer Hi-Fi.

2.0.7 on Android is excellent. Love the generous text length for Album and track names. Love the overall clarity of the interface. Favourites tab is great. Would like to see ability to use it in landscape orientation. On IOS, would like to quick navigation cursor, and album track sort by track no, like on Android. Also now-playing display without the vinyl cover looks better.  Edit - 18/01/2016. Downgrade to 2 stars from 5. Apps repeatly hangs after several tracks. Reports that the Renderer is not responding, or Android OS reports that the app stopped. Suspect some memory problem.
Free version worked on my Android device = paid version didn't!  So much for showing support.  Also artwork would not display for several albums
The free version worked fine so i decided to show my support with this one, only everytime i try to play a track it crashes, most disappointed.
They fixed the issue about the micro SD card. I'm stuck waiting fir a decent media player that can remember where I left off. It should be easy to remember the last played song and start there.

The only player I have found that randomly selects a song from all my music stored on NAS. for this reason alone 5 stars. Some features I would love to see in an update. Persistent notifications and cache of media found in library so it doesn't have to scan every time I start the app.
